London Underground and DLR

The London Underground is a public rapid transit system serving the capital city of United Kingdom, London. It's the world's first underground railway opened in January 1863. It consists of 11 lines and 270 stations.

The Docklands Light Railway (DLR) is a light metro system serving the Docklands area of East London. It is an automated metro system.
